Anyone looking to travel to Caribbean’s “Bahia Principe” resorts @bahiaprincipehotels in Dominican Republic, Mexico and Jamaica should be aware of scammers called “privilege club”, @bpprivilegeclub, operating at their premises. Their representatives, usually working at the resort’s lobby, must be just ignored. They offer to attend so called “no obligation presentation”, where trained sales people trying their best to convince you purchase costly but in fact, absolutely unworthy membership with their “club” for traveling to “Bahia” resorts as a VIP member with allegedly a lot of benefits which in fact later, when there is no way back and money can not be returned, turns out to be nothing but lies. It’s all huge  Fake and Fraud. Stay away from them and be safe!
